Role and Responsibility


  Create BOM and work instruction for assembly level
  Coordinate jigs and tools fabrication with supplier
  Support material &amp; part evaluation from alternative supplier
  Update drawing and release ECR/ECO in Agile
  Set up and validate new tester
  Assist Engineers in problem-solving and troubleshooting

Role Requirements


  Diploma in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent with minimum 2 years of experience in a manufacturing environment.
  Preferably with 3D CAD knowledge/experience (e.g. SolidWorks/Creo)
  Preferably with experience on product assembly and testing.
  Good analytical and problem-solving skills.
  Able to communicate with cross-functional levels.
  Able to work night shift
